{"author":{"id":"222a064dabc38896d34e2f40eca4106beb1a3fa7dfe16ff52f0598bf0153ef39"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1534191669,"nonce":"pKKWVaLoaaJDO5oPfKQ6oYvB/G8=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUzNTAxNzkxMDc=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/2036","origin":"github"},"title":"gzipped input to fastx_trimmer results in incorrect output type","message":"We had a user try to run cutadapt on a file that had been output by fastx_trimmer.  fastx_trimmer had been run using a fastqsanger.gz type input file.  Its output file was labeled as type fastqsanger.gz even though the output was not gzipped, thus cutadapt failed, complaining \"Not a gzipped file\".\n\nI believe the problem is that the output type is set via `format_source=\"input\"` despite the fact that the output is plain ascii which is not subsequently gzipped.  Here are my notes in coming to this conclusion:\n\nThe command that was run as a result of the cutadapt tool was:\n\n`ln -f -s '/galaxy/files/000/364/dataset_364994.dat' 'Trim-data7-1-50.fq.gz' \u0026\u0026    cutadapt      -a 'GeCKO-7-29'='TCTTGTGGAAAGGACGAAACACC'    --untrimmed-output=/galaxy/files/000/364/dataset_364997.dat   --output='out1.gz' --error-rate=0.15 --times=1 --overlap=18         --minimum-length=45     'Trim-data7-1-50.fq.gz'  \u003e report.txt`\n\nThe input `Trim-data7-1-50.fq.gz` has `.gz` in the name (linked by `/galaxy/files/000/364/dataset_364994.dat`), but it isn't gzipped:\n\n```\n[rleach@lirone ~]$ more /galaxy/files/000/364/dataset_364994.dat\n@JLK5VL1:1402:HKVYHBCX2:1:1101:1240:2158 1:N:0:\nTTAGGCTCTTGTGGAAAGGACGAAACACCAAGATCTCCCAAACCCTCTTA\n+\nDDDDDIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIHIHIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIII\n@JLK5VL1:1402:HKVYHBCX2:1:1101:1236:2185 1:N:0:\nCAGATCTCTTGTGGAAAGGACGAAACACCGAGCATCCGCTCTGTCATCCC\n+\n...\n```\n\nIt's type listed in the user's galaxy history is `fastqsanger.gz`.\n\nThat file was produced by:\n\n`zcat -f '/galaxy/files/000/364/dataset_364978.dat' | fastx_trimmer -v -f 1 -l 50 -o '/galaxy/files/000/364/dataset_364994.dat'   -Q 33`\n\nThe fastx_trimmer tool defines the output as:\n\n`\u003cdata name=\"output\" format_source=\"input\" metadata_source=\"input\" /\u003e`\n\nAccording to the documentation, `format_source=\"input\"` means \"data type is the same as that of the input dataset\".\n\nThe command in the XML is preceded by `@CATS@` which is a macro that added the zcat command, and it's followed by `@FQQUAL@`, but there's no conversion of the plain ascii output in that macro to convert the output back to gzip format, thus the output file improperly gets the type `fastqsanger.gz` without any type of corresponding conversion.\n\nA quick fix would be to edit the datatype from `fastqsanger.gz` to `fastqsanger`.  But the real fix would be to correct the wrapper to account for gzipped input formats when creating the output format.","files":null}]}